metabolmics data analysis on breast cancer

sara yusuf

2024-02-16

A total of 27 patients with BC and 30 healthy control subjects were recruited at The Department of Thyroid and Breast Surgery at The Nanxishan Hospital of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region (Guilin, China) before surgery and/or chemotherapy. The study protocol was approved by The Institutional Review Board of the Clinical Research Ethics Committee of Guilin Hospital, and written informed consent was obtained from each subject. The inclusion criteria for patient recruitment was as follows: >18 years old, histologically confirmed BC, no metabolic disease and no previous anticancer treatment. For healthy individuals, there were no abnormalities on their blood tests, physical examinations nor in any imaging studies.

dataset resource: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/metabolights/editor/MTBLS8920/descriptors

perform deferential analysis by lemma

library(limma)
type   = as.character(pheno$condition)

design = model.matrix(~0+factor(type))

colnames(design) = levels(factor(type))



contrast = makeContrasts( cancer - control,levels=design)
fit      = lmFit(as.matrix(data.scaled), design)
fit2     = contrasts.fit(fit, contrast)
fit2     = eBayes(fit2)
res = topTable(fit2, adjust.method='fdr', number=99999999 , p.value = .05 , coef = 1)
